The task guy:<br>
Go to the stone bridge to the east of prydwen keep where the first acolyte quest tells you to go. On the other side of the river beside the bridge is a knight/guard named Sir Alain. He gives you a kill task, you go and kill either a blue or green (to a lvl 5) con mob and go back to him. You get 400 exp points and 140cp. That is 1 bub and 1sp 40cp for about 5 min of your time. I just about lvled doing that until I grouped with some friends. The only main drawback is you usually have to travel for about 1 to 2 min in each direction to find the animal. A couple of examples are: a river spriteling-green- these things live past Prydwen Keep on Sir Alain's side of the river. Grey wolves live on the other side past orange-purple con mobs for about 1 min down the river bank. My advice is: once you have killed your animal, swim back up the middle of the river, this way you avoid all aggro, it is slower but sometimes worth it. Also, you can run away from young boars, hehe I managed to get an orange one chase me halfway down the river. (c: I suggest this becuase if you die, your task immediately comes to an end and you have to go back for another one. <br>
I hope this helps all of you, if you have any questions I am on the Guiny server/Albion and my main chars' name is Sswyftee, from my iksar monk Sswyft.<br>
<br>
Talk to you all later,<br>
